At least 70 students from Anestar boys high school in the county of Nakuru, 10 of whom were arrested at a girls dormitory in the neighboring Anestar precious girls school will be charged upon completion of their KCSE exams. Police say the other 60 boys were found to have been part of a group that planned and sneaked out of their school on Thursday night, and broke into a girls&rsquo; dormitory with their intentions remaining unclear. The school board has opted to send the students far from the school&rsquo;s dormitories even as they continue with their exams.
